export const cityProductCopy: Record<string, string> = {
  'del-mar:roller-shades': `Del Mar Heights homeowners deal with a deceptively demanding sun angle — afternoon light from the southwest hammers west-facing glass with an intensity that bleaches furniture and sends indoor temperatures soaring. Roller shades from iL Progetto LLC are engineered to meet that challenge head-on without sacrificing the canyon and ocean sightlines that make a Del Mar address worth every penny. Our solar-fabric rollers are available in openness factors as low as 1%, giving precise control over glare while still allowing the layered greens of Torrey Hills topography to read clearly from inside. Salt-air-rated hardware means the coastal environment won't compromise the mechanism over time. Call (858) 338-1678 to schedule a complimentary in-home consultation.`,

  'del-mar:zebra-shades': `Few neighborhoods in coastal San Diego demand the dual performance of Olde Del Mar — where historic cottages sit steps from bluff-top views that residents have spent decades protecting. Zebra shades offer the unique alternating sheer-and-solid band system that lets you dial in exactly how much of that Pacific horizon you want visible at any moment of the day. During the notorious marine-layer mornings when light turns flat and diffuse, the sheer bands keep the interior luminous; by afternoon when direct sun tracks across the water, a simple shift to the solid alignment restores comfortable contrast. iL Progetto LLC custom-fabricates each panel to the precise window dimensions found in Del Mar's eclectic mix of mid-century and modern builds. Salt-resistant brackets are standard on every installation. Reach us at (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:cellular-shades': `Energy efficiency rarely tops the conversation in Del Mar — the climate is so temperate that most homeowners assume it doesn't matter. But the reality in Torrey Hills, where east-facing rooms absorb early-morning heat gain and west rooms bake through the afternoon, is that unchecked solar load adds meaningfully to cooling costs. Cellular shades — particularly our dual-cell honeycomb construction — create a genuine insulating air pocket at the glass, moderating that thermal swing without blocking any of the eucalyptus-ridge views residents prize. Because the fabric faces are uniform when viewed from the street, they also satisfy the subtle architectural continuity that Del Mar's design-conscious community quietly enforces. iL Progetto LLC offers both light-filtering and room-darkening cellular options. Call (858) 338-1678 to discuss which cell depth fits your windows.`,

  'del-mar:roman-shades': `There is a particular kind of coastal elegance that shows up in the better homes along Del Mar's canyon rim — a restrained, material-forward aesthetic where every finish is chosen with intention. Roman shades from iL Progetto LLC slot naturally into that vocabulary. We source linen blends, performance weaves, and sheer constructions that fold into crisp horizontal stacks, adding textile warmth to rooms that might otherwise lean too hard on glass and concrete. In Olde Del Mar, where interior designers often work with older windows that carry historical character, a custom Roman shade is frequently the only treatment that respects the original proportions while delivering modern light control. Salt-air-safe mounting hardware protects against the corrosion that ruins cheaper fittings within a season or two. Call us at (858) 338-1678 for fabric samples and a free measure.`,

  'del-mar:wood-aluminum-blinds': `Real wood blinds have a long tradition in Del Mar's hillside homes, but any installer who doesn't account for the marine-layer humidity cycling through the neighborhood is setting a client up for warped slats within a year or two. iL Progetto LLC recommends our hybrid wood-and-aluminum line specifically for Del Mar Heights — the hardwood tilt slats deliver the warm grain appearance homeowners want, while the aluminum ladder tape and moisture-resistant coating prevent the cupping and bowing that straight wood blinds suffer along the coast. The result is a blind that photographs beautifully for real estate listings and performs reliably through June Gloom season and beyond. Our fabrication allows slats in widths that frame canyon views precisely, letting in light from the sky while blocking direct glare. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:shangri-la-shades': `Shangri-La shades — sometimes called silhouette or S-curve shades — occupy a specific design niche that happens to suit Del Mar perfectly: they are soft enough for a coastal interior, precise enough for a modern one, and transparent enough to protect sightlines without surrendering them. In Torrey Hills, where new construction often features oversized fixed windows beside operable casements, a Shangri-La shade provides a continuous softened view of the canyon landscape while gently diffusing the afternoon sun that makes those rooms uncomfortable without treatment. The floating vane construction suspresses glare at the critical late-afternoon angle without the institutional look of a solar roller. iL Progetto LLC carries this product in a range of vane densities suited to Del Mar's solar exposure. Call (858) 338-1678 to see samples at your home.`,

  'del-mar:curtains-drapery': `Drapery in Del Mar is not about blocking the outdoors — it is about framing it. In the estate homes along the Del Mar Heights ridge, floor-to-ceiling drapery panels serve as architectural punctuation, defining the edges of an ocean view rather than concealing it. iL Progetto LLC custom-sews each panel in our San Diego workroom using performance fabrics selected for their resistance to UV fading and the slight mildew risk that comes with marine-layer humidity. We favor European-pleat and ripple-fold headings that stack tightly at the sides, ensuring that when panels are open they occupy minimal visual real estate and the view remains unobstructed. Hardware is powder-coated or solid-brass to resist the salt air that oxidizes lesser finishes. Schedule an in-home design appointment at (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:motorized-shading': `Motorized window treatments make particular sense in Del Mar, where the sun's angle changes dramatically between the marine-layer mornings and the intense southwest exposure of late afternoon — and where many homes have windows positioned above staircases or in double-height great rooms that are simply not reachable by hand. iL Progetto LLC installs quiet DC-motor systems on roller, cellular, and Shangri-La shades throughout Del Mar Heights and Torrey Hills, integrating them with smart-home platforms or programming simple scene presets so every shade adjusts at sunrise and again at the peak afternoon glare window. For the Del Mar homeowner who is frequently away at the beach or traveling, automation also provides the lived-in appearance that deters opportunistic property crime. Call (858) 338-1678 for a smart-shading consultation.`,

  'del-mar:plantation-shutters': `Plantation shutters are the gold standard for resale value and visual permanence in coastal California, and Del Mar is no exception. What separates a well-executed shutter installation from a mediocre one in this market is the louvre width and the tilt-rod choice — details that matter enormously when the product is visible from the street and the neighborhood has an informal but real aesthetic standard. iL Progetto LLC installs solid-basswood shutters with hidden tilt hardware in Olde Del Mar's cottage-style homes and oversized 4.5-inch louvres in the larger contemporary builds in Del Mar Heights, where broad louvres preserve more of the canyon and ocean view when open. Our finish matching to existing millwork is precise enough to fool most painters. Call (858) 338-1678 to schedule a shutter measure.`,

  'del-mar:faux-wood-blinds': `Coastal real estate agents in Del Mar will tell you that the quickest way to devalue a showing is with warped or yellowed window treatments that signal deferred maintenance. Faux-wood blinds from iL Progetto LLC are the practical answer for Del Mar homes where the look of natural wood is desired but the proximity to the ocean — especially in lower-elevation Olde Del Mar — makes real wood a liability. Our PVC-composite faux-wood line holds its shape and color through years of salt-air cycling, morning condensation, and the ultraviolet load that bleaches inferior products within two seasons. They are also fully paintable, which matters in a neighborhood where interior trim colors are sometimes highly specific. Available in 2-inch and 2.5-inch slat widths. Reach iL Progetto LLC at (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:aluminum-blinds': `When a Del Mar homeowner finishes a kitchen or home-office renovation with clean modern lines and needs a window treatment that disappears into the architecture, aluminum blinds are the honest answer. iL Progetto LLC supplies micro-slat aluminum blinds in 1-inch and half-inch profiles that suit the narrower windows common in transitional and contemporary Del Mar Heights builds. The material is inherently salt-air resistant — no warping, no corrosion, no off-gassing — making it one of the more durable coastal options at an accessible price point. Because aluminum blinds are low-profile and light-reflective, they preserve more of the canyon and sky view than fabric alternatives of equivalent light control. We offer them in a wide palette of powder-coat finishes, including several whites and warm grays that coordinate with popular coastal palettes. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:vertical-blinds': `Vertical blinds get underestimated in design conversations, but for the sliding-glass and multi-panel door openings common in Torrey Hills and Del Mar Heights, they remain one of the most functional solutions available. iL Progetto LLC installs fabric-vane verticals in solar-rated materials that block the intense afternoon west exposure while allowing the door panels to operate freely. Unlike horizontal blinds, verticals do not collect the fine coastal dust that infiltrates homes near the bluff, and they are far easier to wipe down. For the open-plan Del Mar home where a glass wall transitions indoor living to a deck with ocean or canyon views, a vertical blind in a sheer solar fabric provides daytime glare management without severing the visual connection to the landscape. Call us at (858) 338-1678 to see fabric options.`,

  'del-mar:panel-track-blinds': `Large glass walls are a defining feature of newer construction in Del Mar Heights, and panel-track systems are purpose-built for those spans. iL Progetto LLC designs panel-track configurations that travel cleanly across openings of eight feet and beyond, using track channels that handle coastal salt exposure without the binding and corrosion that plague cheaper imported hardware. Our panel fabrics for Del Mar are chosen specifically for solar performance — open-weave constructions that let in diffused natural light and maintain the impression of an ocean or canyon view without the glare that makes those rooms unusable in the afternoon. Panel tracks also work exceptionally well as room dividers in open-plan spaces, a popular feature in the contemporary Del Mar builds near Torrey Hills. Reach iL Progetto LLC at (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:woven-wood-shades': `Natural woven-wood shades fit the Del Mar design narrative almost instinctively — the organic texture, the warm honey tones of bamboo and rattan weaves, the way they soften the hard glass and stone that dominate newer coastal homes in Torrey Hills and Del Mar Heights. iL Progetto LLC sources woven-wood shades in constructions dense enough to provide meaningful privacy and light filtering while remaining light and casual in the way the coastal aesthetic demands. Because the weave is inherently open at the edges, we pair them with a privacy liner when needed — a practical consideration in Del Mar Heights, where lots can be surprisingly close together despite the premium price points. The natural materials also align with the biophilic interior direction many Del Mar designers are pursuing. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:sheer-shades': `Morning light in Del Mar is something architects specifically design for — the soft, diffused luminosity that arrives before the marine layer burns off is unlike anything the inland valleys receive. Sheer shades from iL Progetto LLC are engineered to preserve that quality of light inside the home. By suspending horizontal fabric vanes between two layers of translucent sheer, they simultaneously soften direct sun and maintain the visual connection to the canyon and coastal landscape that Del Mar homeowners protect so fiercely. In Olde Del Mar, where bungalow windows are often oriented to frame specific views of the bluff or the village below, sheer shades allow that framing to remain active all day — adjusting vane angle as the light shifts rather than simply closing down. Call (858) 338-1678 for an in-home demonstration.`,

  'del-mar:blackout-curtains': `Sleep quality in Del Mar is disrupted by two separate light sources that most people don't anticipate when they move to the coast: the eastern glow off the ocean at dawn, which arrives earlier and brighter than expected, and the ambient light that spills from street fixtures and neighboring properties on the narrow residential lanes of Olde Del Mar. iL Progetto LLC custom-fabricates blackout curtains with a true triple-pass blackout lining, side returns, and ceiling-mount track options that eliminate light ingress from all edges — not just through the fabric face. For primary bedrooms in Del Mar Heights where morning sun rises directly over the canyon, this level of light control is transformative. Fabric selections range from minimal linen-look solids to richly textured designs. Call (858) 338-1678 to schedule a consultation.`,

  'del-mar:sheer-drapes': `Sheer drapery at the right scale can make a Del Mar living room feel as if the Pacific is simply an extension of the interior — the fabric diffuses and softens the connection rather than cutting it. iL Progetto LLC makes sheer drapes in extra-wide panels for the tall windows common in newer Del Mar Heights builds, using performance sheer fabrics that resist the UV degradation and subtle yellowing that coastal sun inflicts on cheaper sheers within a season or two. The ripple-fold heading we favor keeps panels consistently spaced and neat even in the sea breeze that moves through open windows during summer evenings. For rooms where privacy is not the primary concern but glare is, a floor-to-ceiling sheer in a solar-performance fabric solves both issues elegantly. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:motorized-exterior': `Exterior motorized shading is still relatively rare in Del Mar, which means the homeowners who install it gain a meaningful comfort advantage over neighbors relying solely on interior treatments. By intercepting solar heat before it reaches the glass, exterior roller screens and zip shades from iL Progetto LLC reduce cooling loads by as much as 80% on exposed elevations — a significant number for the west and southwest facades in Torrey Hills and Del Mar Heights that take the full force of afternoon sun. Salt-air-rated aluminum extrusions and marine-grade guide cables are standard in every coastal installation we do. The systems motorize to preset positions and integrate with smart-home platforms. For homeowners doing new construction or major remodels, exterior shading at the rough stage is far simpler to run. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:sun-screens': `Sun screens — also called solar screens or exterior insect screens — are one of the most underutilized tools in coastal San Diego window management, and Del Mar is no exception. iL Progetto LLC installs exterior solar-screen frames on west and southwest exposures throughout Del Mar Heights and Torrey Hills, where afternoon sun is the dominant comfort complaint from homeowners. Unlike interior shades, a solar screen intercepts radiation before it enters the glass cavity, preventing heat buildup and allowing windows to remain open for the ocean breeze without glare pouring across the room. Our screen fabric selections range from 80% to 90% blockage factors, and we offer charcoal weaves that preserve outward views far better than darker alternatives. The frames are powder-coated aluminum rated for salt-air exposure. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'del-mar:awnings': `A retractable awning over a Del Mar deck or patio does something no interior window treatment can: it expands the usable living space by creating a shaded outdoor room during the afternoon hours when the sun makes unshaded terraces uncomfortable. iL Progetto LLC installs motorized retractable awnings with wind sensors throughout Del Mar Heights and Olde Del Mar, using aluminum cassette housings that protect the fabric from the marine-layer moisture that causes mildew on exposed awnings. Our awning fabrics are UV-stable, solution-dyed acrylic that resist the salt-air fading that degrades lesser materials within a few seasons. Because Del Mar lots vary significantly in orientation, we design each awning projection and pitch specifically to the solar angle and deck geometry. Retractable systems also mean the awning stores cleanly when not needed. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:roller-shades': `Living in Leucadia means embracing a certain relationship with the sun — the morning marine layer burns off by 10 a.m. and the UV index climbs to levels that, over years, will fade artwork, dry out wood floors, and bleach upholstery if windows are left unmanaged. Roller shades from iL Progetto LLC address this directly with our solar-fabric line, which is rated to block 99% of UV radiation even at openness factors that keep the room feeling connected to the garden. Leucadia's biophilic interior design direction — living walls, natural stone, reclaimed wood — depends on controlled, quality light rather than raw sun exposure, and a well-specified solar roller provides exactly that tonal balance. We stock fabrics in warm naturals and earthy neutrals that coordinate with the organic palette Encinitas designers favor. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:zebra-shades': `Cardiff-by-the-Sea is named for something — the moody, layered coastal light that shifts from silver-gray in the morning to blinding white by midday. Zebra shades handle that range in a way simpler products cannot. The alternating sheer and solid bands provide a continuously adjustable balance between privacy and openness, making them ideal for Cardiff homes where the street and the surf are sometimes visible from the same window. iL Progetto LLC installs zebra shades in fabrics sourced for natural texture and muted color — jute-tone sheers and warm ivory solids that feel intentional in the earthy, design-conscious Encinitas interior rather than merely functional. Because the mechanism is a continuous loop, there are no cords for child-safety concerns, which matters in the family-oriented neighborhoods throughout Cardiff. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free estimate.`,

  'encinitas:cellular-shades': `Olivenhain sits inland from the coast, elevated and exposed in a way that separates it thermally from the beach communities to the west — hotter summers, cooler winters, and a UV load that is more direct than the marine-layer-softened light reaching Cardiff and Leucadia. Cellular shades from iL Progetto LLC are the most thermally intelligent window treatment available for Olivenhain's conditions, with the dual-cell honeycomb construction creating a stable insulating barrier that keeps conditioned air where it belongs. For the equestrian estate homes in Olivenhain where windows are large and numerous, cellular shades also deliver consistent aesthetics across every opening — the same clean, minimalist face on every window, in the earthy whites and warm grays that read naturally against the oak woodland and sandstone that characterize this neighborhood. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:roman-shades': `Roman shades hit a specific frequency that Encinitas homeowners respond to — they are soft without being fussy, structured without being cold, and when made in the right fabric they carry an unmistakably organic character that suits the biophilic design direction running through Leucadia and Cardiff interiors. iL Progetto LLC fabricates Romans in relaxed flat-fold and hobbled styles, using linen, cotton-jute blends, and performance wovens with the natural hand and texture that Encinitas designers specify. Unlike roller shades, a Roman introduces actual textile depth to the window — the horizontal folds create shadow and dimension that read beautifully in the soft coastal morning light. For the beach-close bungalows of Leucadia where rooms are smaller and finishes more curated, a custom Roman is frequently the single highest-impact window decision a homeowner can make. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:wood-aluminum-blinds': `Wood blinds feel at home in Encinitas in a way they don't quite achieve in more manicured coastal cities — the grain, the warmth, the honesty of the material resonates with the biophilic values that drive interior choices throughout Leucadia and Cardiff. iL Progetto LLC's hybrid wood-aluminum line gives Encinitas homeowners that natural material story while engineering out the moisture vulnerability that straight basswood blinds can't survive in the marine-layer humidity cycling through coastal neighborhoods. The aluminum ladder system and moisture-sealed tilt mechanism hold up through June Gloom season without the slat warping or finish lifting that ruins less-considered wood blinds. Available in stain tones from whitewash through dark walnut, they complement the reclaimed-wood shelving and natural stone that Encinitas interiors favor. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:shangri-la-shades': `The biophilic design movement has taken hold firmly in Encinitas — more firmly, perhaps, than anywhere else in coastal San Diego — and Shangri-La shades are a natural fit for that direction. The soft floating vanes suspended between sheer fabric layers create a luminous, layered quality of light that mimics the diffusion of sunlight through a forest canopy, which is precisely the effect that biophilic designers seek. For the newer single-family homes in Cardiff with large south-facing glazing, Shangri-La shades manage the morning and midday sun load while maintaining the interior's visual connection to outdoor planting and sky. iL Progetto LLC offers this product in warm sheer tones — sand, ivory, warm white — that harmonize with the natural material palettes dominant in Encinitas interiors. Call (858) 338-1678 for samples.`,

  'encinitas:curtains-drapery': `Encinitas has always been a town where interior design choices carry a certain self-expression — the eclectic, artist-adjacent personality of Leucadia shows up in homes where a drapery panel is chosen as much for its material story as for its function. iL Progetto LLC custom-sews drapery in our San Diego workroom using linen-cotton blends, sheer performance weaves, and natural textiles that speak to the organic interior direction the Encinitas market favors. We avoid the stiff, synthetic sheens that read as formal — instead, our fabrications favor softly tailored pleats and relaxed ripple folds that move naturally in the coastal breeze. For the taller windows in newer Olivenhain homes, we engineer floor-to-ceiling panels with the proper fullness ratio to achieve that casual-luxe quality that makes a room feel complete. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:motorized-shading': `Motorized shading in Encinitas is less about luxury and more about a genuine quality-of-life upgrade for homeowners who have invested in thoughtful interiors and don't want to fight with manual treatments every time the marine layer shifts. iL Progetto LLC programs simple sun-tracking scenes into our motorized roller and cellular systems — shades lower automatically when measured solar intensity crosses a threshold that would begin fading floor finishes or creating glare on work surfaces. In Cardiff, where many homeowners work from home in spaces that front the ocean or a garden, automated shading means consistent, comfortable light without constant manual adjustments. All motors are quiet DC systems that won't disturb the calm, natural-sound environment Encinitas residents cultivate. Reach us at (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:plantation-shutters': `Plantation shutters represent the longest-lasting investment in window treatments, and Encinitas homeowners — particularly in the larger homes in Olivenhain — respond to that permanence. iL Progetto LLC installs solid-basswood plantation shutters that are painted and primed in our shop before installation, ensuring a finish quality that holds up against the UV exposure and salt-air humidity that cycle through coastal neighborhoods. In Leucadia, where bungalow windows are often irregular and older, our custom-mill capability allows us to fabricate shutters for openings that off-the-shelf products cannot accommodate. The louvre tilt adjusts to manage the high UV of late-morning sun while maintaining the laid-back, open feeling that Encinitas lifestyles demand. A shutter installation also adds measurable resale value in a market as design-aware as this one. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:faux-wood-blinds': `Not every home in Encinitas is positioned for a premium window-treatment budget, but that doesn't mean the treatment should look cheap. iL Progetto LLC's faux-wood blind line delivers the warm slat profile and natural-tone color palette of real wood in a PVC-composite construction that holds up flawlessly in the marine-layer humidity cycling through Cardiff and Leucadia. The material is inherently resistant to the warping and finish lifting that eliminates real wood as a practical choice in homes within a mile or two of the beach. Our faux-wood blinds are also fully cordless, which aligns with Encinitas's strong child-safety consciousness and removes the cord-management anxiety that comes with older blind designs. Available in warm whites, honey tones, and driftwood grays that suit the natural Encinitas palette. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:aluminum-blinds': `Aluminum blinds don't typically top Encinitas design wishlists, but in the right application — a coastal mudroom, a breakfast nook, a home office with utilitarian priorities — they are the most durable, clean, and salt-air-resistant option available. iL Progetto LLC supplies micro-slat aluminum blinds in the muted, earthy finishes that don't clash with Encinitas's natural material interiors: warm white, linen, soft taupe, and driftwood tones that read as intentional rather than institutional. In the beach-close homes of Cardiff where moisture from open windows and wet swimwear is a constant presence, an aluminum blind on a utility window handles the environment that would ruin fabric products. Low-profile valances keep the installation looking current and considered. Contact iL Progetto at (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:vertical-blinds': `The broad sliding glass doors that open Encinitas homes to their outdoor spaces — the coastal garden, the fire-pit patio, the pool deck — present a covering challenge that vertical blinds resolve better than most alternatives. iL Progetto LLC installs fabric-vane verticals in solar-rated sheer constructions for these openings, giving Encinitas homeowners the ability to modulate direct sun without losing the indoor-outdoor flow that the beach lifestyle demands. The vane angle adjusts to track the morning sun that enters through east-facing door walls in Cardiff's low-lying homes, and the entire assembly stacks neatly to one side when the doors are open for maximum airflow. We carry the product in natural linen tones and warm sheers that feel organic and intentional in the biophilic Encinitas interior. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:panel-track-blinds': `Encinitas architecture has been shifting toward larger, more open floor plans — particularly in the newer Olivenhain builds — and panel-track systems are the most design-forward solution for the wide window and door openings those plans produce. iL Progetto LLC's panel-track configurations use precision-machined aluminum tracks that glide silently and resist the corrosion that salt air introduces at any distance from the beach. Panel fabrics are selected for UV performance and natural aesthetics: grasscloth-inspired wovens, warm solar sheers, and textured naturals that bring material interest to a large window wall without visual noise. For the homeowner who wants the light management of a blind and the material warmth of a shade in a single streamlined product, a panel track in the right fabric achieves both. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:woven-wood-shades': `Woven wood shades — bamboo, seagrass, rattan, jute — are practically the unofficial window treatment of Encinitas. The organic materiality, the warm light they transmit, and the relaxed-but-intentional character they bring to a room fit the neighborhood's design identity more precisely than almost any other product category. iL Progetto LLC carries an extensive woven-wood selection from tightly woven privacy constructions to open, airy weaves that simply filter and tint incoming light in the amber tones of natural fiber. For Leucadia homes where interiors lean heavily on reclaimed wood, natural plaster, and live-edge furniture, a woven-wood shade ties the window into the material story of the room rather than sitting apart from it as a functional afterthought. Lining options available for privacy. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:sheer-shades': `Sheer shades are ideally suited to the quality of light that Encinitas receives — soft, layered, and directionally variable in a way that flat solar exposure isn't. iL Progetto LLC's sheer shade line uses suspended horizontal vanes between two translucent fabric layers to sculpt that incoming light, diffusing the harsh high-UV midday sun while preserving the luminous quality of the marine-softened morning. In Cardiff, where living rooms often orient toward a garden or a borrowed coastal view, sheer shades allow that green-and-light connection to remain alive all day without the glare peaks that make untreated windows uncomfortable. The vane angle adjusts continuously, meaning the same shade that protects at noon provides full view transparency in the evening. Available in warm natural tones. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:blackout-curtains': `Encinitas has a significant population of people who work nonstandard hours — remote workers, surfers chasing early tides, service-industry professionals — and quality sleep at unconventional times is a genuine need that blackout curtains address better than any other product. iL Progetto LLC fabricates triple-pass blackout curtains with side-return panels and ceiling-close tracks for primary bedrooms throughout Leucadia and Cardiff, eliminating the light intrusion from the eastern sky that wakes coastal residents at 5:30 a.m. during summer months. We pair the blackout lining with natural-texture face fabrics — linen, cotton-linen blend, soft performance weaves — so the curtain reads as a considered design choice from inside the room rather than a blackout afterthought. UV-resistant construction prevents the lining from yellowing over time. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:sheer-drapes': `Sheer drapery in Encinitas functions as a light-quality control device as much as a privacy tool — the goal is the continuation of that soft, coastal luminosity that makes these rooms feel genuinely restorative. iL Progetto LLC sews sheer drapes in extra-wide widths using UV-stable performance sheers that resist the yellowing and fiber degradation that coastal UV inflicts on lesser fabrics. For the informal, lived-in rooms of Leucadia bungalows where a floor-to-ceiling sheer might be the only window layer, we recommend sheer weights with enough opacity to provide evening privacy without losing the airy daytime character. Ripple-fold and pencil-pleat headings are our most requested styles in this market — the first for contemporary homes, the second for rooms with a relaxed-historic character. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:motorized-exterior': `Exterior motorized shading for Encinitas homes offers something interior products cannot: the ability to stop solar heat before it enters the structure, which dramatically reduces cooling load on the exposed south and west elevations common in Olivenhain. iL Progetto LLC installs zip-guide roller screens and cassette-style exterior roller shades using hardware engineered for coastal exposure — anodized aluminum extrusions, stainless-steel guide cables, and UV-stable fabric that won't degrade under the high-UV Encinitas sky. For homeowners building or renovating in Olivenhain, exterior motorized shading at the rough-construction stage simplifies the structural integration and reduces finished-cost significantly. The systems integrate with smart-home platforms and include wind sensors that retract the shade automatically during coastal gusts. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:sun-screens': `Sun screens installed on the exterior of Encinitas windows are one of the highest-return investments in home comfort a coastal homeowner can make — they intercept 80-90% of solar heat before it reaches the glass, allow windows to remain open for the ocean breeze, and reduce UV exposure to interior finishes without making rooms feel enclosed. iL Progetto LLC custom-fabricates exterior solar-screen frames in powder-coated aluminum for all window sizes and shapes common throughout Cardiff, Leucadia, and Olivenhain. Our charcoal-weave screens in 80% and 90% blockage factors provide the heat and UV reduction without visually darkening the room interior, because the contrast between inside and outside remains favorable. They are removable for seasonal cleaning and virtually maintenance-free in the coastal environment. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'encinitas:awnings': `An awning over an Encinitas deck changes the entire seasonal calendar of that outdoor space — suddenly the May and June hours when unshaded patios are uncomfortable become usable, and the south-facing decks in Olivenhain that bake through the afternoon become genuine outdoor rooms. iL Progetto LLC installs motorized retractable awnings with cassette housings that protect the acrylic fabric from the marine-layer moisture that causes mildew on exposed awning fabric. Wind sensors retract the awning automatically during the afternoon coastal gusts that arrive in summer. For the biophilic Encinitas homeowner who has invested in an outdoor living space with native plantings, a retractable awning extends the useful hours of that space without blocking the sky when shade isn't needed. Fabric options in warm naturals and coastal stripes. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:roller-shades': `Privacy is the defining window-treatment challenge in Solana Beach, and nowhere is that more apparent than in the densely built streets near Fletcher Cove, where homes sit close together and neighbors' sightlines intersect at uncomfortable angles. iL Progetto LLC installs solar-fabric roller shades in blockout and room-darkening constructions that restore daytime privacy to these tight-lot homes without requiring residents to live in artificial darkness. Our fascia-style roller systems present a clean, finished appearance from the street — important in a neighborhood where the Cedros Design District has raised the design expectations of the entire community. We offer dual-roller configurations that allow a sheer solar screen for daytime UV management and a privacy liner for evening use, both in a single compact headrail. Call (858) 338-1678 for a free measure.`,

  'solana-beach:zebra-shades': `Solana Beach's Cedros Design District has trained the local homeowner to notice when a window treatment is well-considered versus merely functional — the block is full of design showrooms, fabric studios, and furniture galleries, and the clientele shops with educated eyes. Zebra shades from iL Progetto LLC are precisely the kind of product that passes that scrutiny: the clean-lined banding system, the quality of motion in a well-engineered cassette, the way the fabric transitions between open and privacy modes with a smooth, intentional feel. For the homes in Solana Hills where morning sun is a privacy concern — neighbors visible through east-facing windows before the sun climbs — zebra shades give precise control at each window independently. We carry the product in design-forward colorways. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:cellular-shades': `The narrow lots and close proximity of homes near Fletcher Cove create a specific acoustic and thermal challenge that doesn't get discussed enough: the heat island effect of adjoining walls, and the noise transmission from neighbors and the beach access traffic that moves through these streets during summer. Cellular shades from iL Progetto LLC contribute meaningfully to both issues — the honeycomb air pockets provide genuine thermal insulation, moderating the solar gain on south and west elevations, and the dense fabric faces provide a measure of acoustic softening that bare glass cannot. For the smaller, tightly planned homes characteristic of beachside Solana Beach, cellular shades also maintain a uniform, clean exterior appearance that the neighborhood's design-conscious standard expects. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:roman-shades': `The Cedros Design District has made Solana Beach a small-city design destination — interior designers, architects, and homeowners with genuine aesthetic literacy are the core population here. Roman shades from iL Progetto LLC serve that client well because they are, fundamentally, a designed object: the flat fold, the fabric selection, the trim detail, the mount precision all contribute to a finished result that rewards attention. We fabricate Romans in a wide range of designer fabrics including performance linens, outdoor-rated weaves suitable for the high-UV Solana Beach environment, and imported textiles sourced from our network of San Diego design-trade vendors. For the Solana Hills home with a beautiful breakfast nook that also happens to face a neighbor's window directly, a Roman in a quality opaque fabric solves the privacy problem beautifully. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:wood-aluminum-blinds': `Wood blinds in Solana Beach face a tougher coastal environment than the marketing materials typically admit — the proximity to the ocean, the morning condensation that forms on windows facing Solana Hills' east-facing slopes, and the UV intensity that comes without the marine-layer buffering of more sheltered locations all work against straight-wood products. iL Progetto LLC's hybrid wood-aluminum blind is the answer: real wood slats with aluminum moisture-resistant hardware and ladder tape that doesn't absorb the humidity cycling through a beachside home. The result looks indistinguishable from a premium real-wood blind and performs decades better in this environment. For privacy-conscious Solana Beach homeowners who want the ability to tilt slats precisely to block neighbor sightlines while retaining sky views, the 2.5-inch slat width provides that fine-grained control. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:shangri-la-shades': `Shangri-La shades occupy a design category — refined, luminous, architecturally aware — that aligns naturally with the Cedros Design District's aesthetic standard. iL Progetto LLC installs this product throughout Solana Beach in rooms where the challenge is managing the bright, direct coastal sun while maintaining the feeling of light and space that smaller beach homes need to avoid feeling cramped. The floating vane construction suppresses glare without blocking light transmission entirely, making rooms feel brighter and more open than a privacy roller in the same space would. For the narrow lots near Fletcher Cove where a front-room window faces a neighbor's fence at close range, a Shangri-La shade in a warm sheer provides full daytime privacy while the vane angle still allows north and south sky light to fill the room. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:curtains-drapery': `Drapery in Solana Beach earns its place in the design conversation because of the Cedros Design District influence — homeowners here don't choose window treatments the way they might in a less design-saturated community. iL Progetto LLC custom-sews drapery panels in our San Diego workroom using fabrics selected from our trade line, which includes performance sheers, indoor-outdoor weaves appropriate for the salt-air environment, and luxurious natural textiles for rooms set back from direct ocean exposure. Privacy is a recurring theme in our Solana Beach consultations — the close lot spacing means that drapery panels that stack away from the window during the day need to close with genuine opacity at night. We design every drapery order to meet that functional brief along with the aesthetic one. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:motorized-shading': `Motorized shading in Solana Beach solves a specific privacy problem: the timing of natural light and neighbor activity doesn't always align with a homeowner's manual adjustment habits, and in the tight lots near Fletcher Cove, leaving a window uncovered at the wrong moment means an inadvertent view into a private interior. iL Progetto LLC programs our motorized roller and cellular systems to close automatically on sunset schedules, ensuring the evening privacy that Solana Beach's close-together homes require without depending on residents to remember to lower shades at dusk. During the day, solar-sensor automation lowers glare-blocking rollers when afternoon sun intensity reaches a set threshold, then retracts them as conditions change. The systems are quiet, reliable, and compatible with all major smart-home platforms. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:plantation-shutters': `Plantation shutters are a perennial favorite in Solana Beach for the privacy they provide through louvre-angle adjustment — a functionality that the close-lot nature of neighborhoods like Solana Hills and the streets off Fletcher Cove makes genuinely necessary rather than optional. iL Progetto LLC installs solid-basswood shutters with the tilt precision and material quality that the Cedros Design District clientele expects. Our hidden tilt rod option eliminates the center bar that splits ocean and garden views, and our waterproof MDF shutter line is the right call for the bathrooms and laundry rooms of beachside homes where moisture is a constant. For street-facing windows in dense Solana Beach neighborhoods, a half-height café-style shutter allows natural light from the upper glass while the lower panel closed ensures complete privacy at street level. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:faux-wood-blinds': `Faux-wood blinds are a workhorse product in Solana Beach — durable, moisture-resistant, and priced accessibly enough for the full-house window treatment projects that newly purchased beach homes often require. iL Progetto LLC's PVC-composite faux-wood line is specifically suited to the Solana Beach environment, resisting the warping, yellowing, and finish-lift that real wood experiences at ocean proximity. For the tight-lot homes near Fletcher Cove where privacy is the primary requirement, the 2.5-inch slat width allows precise tilt adjustment to block neighbor sightlines while angling sky light into the room. We carry the product in the coastal palette — driftwood, white wash, and warm white — that suits the light, airy interiors common in Solana Beach homes. Cordless options are available. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:aluminum-blinds': `Aluminum blinds are not the most glamorous product in the catalog, but in the specific context of Solana Beach vacation rentals, secondary homes, and the utility spaces in design-forward residences near the Cedros Design District, they are the most practical. iL Progetto LLC supplies aluminum blinds in micro-slat profiles in the quiet neutral tones that don't clash with curated interiors — warm white, linen, and natural aluminum — with moisture-resistant construction that handles the condensation and humidity common in beachside homes. For investment properties in Solana Beach where window treatments need to survive high tenant turnover without deteriorating, aluminum blinds offer a longevity that fabric products simply can't match in this environment. We install throughout Solana Hills and the beach areas. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:vertical-blinds': `The sliding door openings that connect Solana Beach homes to their small patios and outdoor showers — ubiquitous in the beachside residential blocks near Fletcher Cove — are where vertical blinds deliver their most unambiguous value. iL Progetto LLC installs fabric-vane vertical systems on these openings in privacy-rated fabrics that block neighbor sightlines when the patio is in use, while the entire assembly stacks cleanly to the side when the door is open and full airflow is the priority. The salt-air resistance of the aluminum headrail and wand mechanism is a practical consideration that cheaper vertical systems fail — we source hardware rated specifically for coastal environments. For Solana Beach homes with south-facing patios that get direct afternoon sun, we carry solar-fabric vane options. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:panel-track-blinds': `The Cedros Design District influence makes Solana Beach homeowners unusually attuned to the visual coherence of a window wall — which is exactly the scenario where panel-track blinds excel over products that introduce multiple hardware points. iL Progetto LLC designs panel-track configurations for large window openings throughout Solana Beach using precision aluminum tracks and panel fabrics selected for their visual weight and solar performance. The minimal, architectural appearance of a well-installed panel track reads as deliberate and considered — the kind of design decision that reflects the Cedros Design District aesthetic awareness of the surrounding neighborhood. For the privacy concerns specific to Solana Beach's close-lot conditions, we specify opaque or room-darkening panel fabrics that provide full daytime privacy without sacrificing the clean, linear appearance of the system. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:woven-wood-shades': `Woven-wood shades bring warmth and texture to Solana Beach interiors without the decorative heaviness of drapery — important in the smaller, beach-proximity homes near Fletcher Cove where rooms need light management but not additional visual weight. iL Progetto LLC carries woven-wood in an extensive range of bamboo, rattan, and seagrass constructions, from tightly woven panels that provide genuine privacy to airy open weaves that simply texture and filter the incoming coastal light. For the design-aware Solana Beach clientele shaped by proximity to the Cedros Design District, woven-wood is often the product that resolves the tension between wanting something beautiful and wanting something that performs. Privacy liners are available and recommended for windows facing neighboring properties — a practical consideration in this dense coastal community. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:sheer-shades': `Sheer shades are a privacy-enabling product that most homeowners don't realize they need until they install them — the floating vane system lets in natural light while making interior spaces invisible from outside during daylight hours, which is the precise scenario that Solana Beach's tight-lot neighborhoods near Fletcher Cove present. iL Progetto LLC installs sheer shades throughout Solana Beach in warm, soft fabric tones that complement the casual coastal interior direction of the neighborhood. The continuous vane-angle adjustment allows the homeowner to balance the competing demands of morning privacy (east-facing windows before the sun rises high enough to shift the inside-outside light differential) and afternoon glare management (west-facing glass in the late afternoon). For the Cedros Design District clientele who wants performance and aesthetics in a single product, sheer shades are a strong answer. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:blackout-curtains': `Solana Beach summers bring a street-level energy — beach foot traffic, car doors, early-morning surfboarders — that translates into light and sound intrusion in the bedrooms of homes close to Fletcher Cove and the access paths. iL Progetto LLC fabricates blackout curtains with true triple-pass blackout lining for Solana Beach primary bedrooms, combining the light elimination that coastal sleepers need with face fabrics chosen to look intentional in well-designed rooms. Our ceiling-mount track system allows panels to close with no gap at the top — the most common light-leak point in standard curtain installations. For vacation properties in Solana Beach where guest sleep quality is a priority, blackout curtains in the bedroom are a consistently mentioned positive factor in rental reviews. We offer both fabrication and professional installation. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:sheer-drapes': `Sheer drapes in Solana Beach serve a privacy function that is specific to the coastal light conditions: during daylight hours, when interior light levels are lower than exterior, a translucent sheer fabric makes it genuinely difficult to see inside a home from the street or a neighboring window — providing privacy without blackout. iL Progetto LLC sews sheer drapery in UV-stable performance fabrics that resist the coastal yellowing that affects lesser sheers within a single season. For the design-aware Solana Beach client in the Cedros Design District orbit, we carry sheer constructions with a refined quality of hand and drape that reads as a genuine textile selection rather than an afterthought. Floor-to-ceiling sheers on large windows also amplify the feeling of space in smaller beachside homes. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:motorized-exterior': `Exterior motorized shading in the homes along Solana Beach's coast-adjacent blocks is a heat-management tool that interior products cannot replicate — by stopping solar radiation before it reaches the glass, exterior roller screens eliminate the heat buildup that makes west-facing rooms uncomfortable in the afternoon without requiring air conditioning to run continuously. iL Progetto LLC installs cassette-style motorized exterior rollers with zip-guide systems in hardware rated for the salt-air environment — anodized aluminum, marine-grade stainless hardware, UV-stable solution-dyed fabric. Privacy is a secondary benefit worth noting: an exterior screen in an opaque or semi-opaque construction also blocks street-level sightlines from the densely traveled beach-access paths near Fletcher Cove. Wind sensors retract the screens automatically during coastal gusts. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'solana-beach:sun-screens': `Exterior solar screens on Solana Beach homes solve the summer afternoon problem on west-facing facades — the sun angle at 4 p.m. in June drives heat through glass faster than most air conditioning systems can compensate, and interior shades only manage the heat after it has already entered the room. iL Progetto LLC custom-fabricates exterior solar screen frames in powder-coated aluminum sized precisely to each window opening throughout Solana Hills and the beachside residential blocks. Our screen fabric in charcoal 80% blockage provides the thermal performance without noticeably darkening the interior — a common objection to exterior screens that this specific fabric dispels. The product is removable for cleaning and durable enough to handle years of the coastal environment without degradation. Call (858) 338-1678 for a measure appointment.`,

  'solana-beach:awnings': `Awnings over Solana Beach patios perform a dual function that is specific to this tight-lot neighborhood: they provide shade for the patio occupant and, when properly sized, they block the sightline from upper-level neighboring windows that look down onto the outdoor space. iL Progetto LLC installs motorized retractable awnings with cassette housings in solution-dyed acrylic fabrics proven to resist the salt-air fading and mildew that affect lesser products in the coastal environment. For the small patios near Fletcher Cove where outdoor space is precious and privacy from adjacent properties is limited, a well-engineered awning is one of the most practical outdoor investments available. Wind sensors retract the awning automatically when coastal gusts threaten. Reach iL Progetto LLC at (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:roller-shades': `The Architectural Review Board of The Covenant in Rancho Santa Fe maintains standards that few residential communities in California can match — and any window treatment visible from the exterior must meet those standards in material quality, color, and presentation. iL Progetto LLC works within ARB submission processes routinely, specifying roller shades with fascia cassettes in custom-matched powder-coat finishes that present a neutral, architecturally harmonious appearance from the street while delivering precision solar management inside the estate. On the expansive west-facing glass walls common in Mediterranean-plan homes throughout The Covenant, our solar-fabric rollers in 1% and 3% openness factors control the late-afternoon sun load while preserving the landscape views that these properties are designed around. Call (858) 338-1678 for a consultation.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:zebra-shades': `Rancho Santa Fe's estate properties, particularly in Fairbanks Ranch and Del Rayo Estates, are designed with an interior scale that demands window treatments of genuine substance — products that look considered in a room with 12-foot ceilings, limestone floors, and custom millwork. Zebra shades from iL Progetto LLC are fabricated in wider widths and taller drops than most manufacturers accommodate, using double-faced banding constructions in warm naturals and architectural neutrals that suit Mediterranean and Spanish Colonial interiors. The alternating sheer-and-solid band system provides the daytime privacy management that indoor-staff households require — controlling who can see in from the service and arrival areas — while maintaining the luminous, open quality of a luxury interior. Call (858) 338-1678 to arrange an estate consultation.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:cellular-shades': `Energy efficiency at the estate scale in Rancho Santa Fe carries real financial consequence — when a single home has forty or sixty windows, the thermal performance of each window treatment multiplies significantly across the building envelope. iL Progetto LLC specifies dual-cell honeycomb cellular shades for the Cielo and Fairbanks Ranch estate homes where summer cooling costs are substantial, using deeper cell constructions for the high-solar-load south and west elevations and single-cell options on the cooler north-facing rooms. The exterior appearance of cellular shades is uniform and neutral — a consistent presentation important to The Covenant's ARB standards, which govern any window treatment visible from the motor court or street. Fabric colorways are available in the soft whites and warm ivories that read correctly behind Spanish Colonial fenestration. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:roman-shades': `Roman shades in the formal rooms of Rancho Santa Fe's Mediterranean estate homes carry a heritage that is entirely appropriate — the style originates in the Roman atrium and has been associated with high-quality residential interiors for centuries. iL Progetto LLC custom-fabricates flat-fold Romans for the formal living and dining rooms of The Covenant properties using imported linens, hand-woven silks, and performance textiles sourced from our design-trade network. At the estate scale, Roman shades are almost always part of a layered treatment — operating in concert with drapery panels on a motorized system — which requires precise fabrication tolerances that only a workroom accustomed to luxury-tier projects can deliver. Our pattern-matching capability for repeat fabrics is exact. Call (858) 338-1678 to begin a design consultation.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:wood-aluminum-blinds': `Wood blinds on the interior of Rancho Santa Fe's estate properties project a quiet material authority that suits the lifestyle of The Covenant and Fairbanks Ranch — the grain and warmth of real wood, the precision tilt of a well-engineered slat, the deep color of a rich stain. iL Progetto LLC's hybrid wood-aluminum line delivers that premium material appearance with the moisture-resistant engineering that prevents the warping and finish failures that interior humidity cycling causes in pure-wood products. At the scale of a Rancho Santa Fe estate, where a single great room may have twelve identical windows that all need to match, the consistency of our finish program — stained, painted, and custom-match options — ensures uniformity across every opening. The aluminum tilt mechanism provides a lifespan consistent with the luxury standard these homes demand. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:shangri-la-shades': `The scale and materiality of Rancho Santa Fe's interior design vocabulary — the heavy plaster, the hand-hewn beams, the antique stone floors of The Covenant's historic haciendas — asks for a window treatment that brings luminosity without competing with those architectural elements. Shangri-La shades from iL Progetto LLC are precisely calibrated for that role. The floating vane construction transforms direct sun into a soft, directional glow that enhances Spanish Colonial interiors rather than flattening them. In the large formal rooms of Del Rayo Estates, where windows are often arched or deeply recessed, our fabrication team works with the specific geometry of each opening to ensure the shade mounts and operates correctly. We carry the product in warm ivory, champagne, and architectural white tones suited to the Rancho Santa Fe palette. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:curtains-drapery': `Custom drapery at the luxury standard expected in Rancho Santa Fe requires a fabrication approach that is categorically different from residential retail — the header construction, the interlining weight, the hem weighting, the return depth, and the track engineering all contribute to a finished product that performs and presents at an estate level. iL Progetto LLC custom-sews all drapery in our San Diego workroom, working with designer-specified fabrics or guiding clients through our trade-exclusive fabric program. For the formal entertaining rooms of Fairbanks Ranch and Cielo properties, we work with interior designers and ARB consultants to ensure that exterior-facing drapery meets The Covenant's exterior appearance standards while achieving the luxury interior result the client expects. Every panel is precisely weighted and finished. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:motorized-shading': `At the estate scale of Rancho Santa Fe's larger properties — Cielo, Del Rayo Estates, Fairbanks Ranch — manually operating forty or more individual window treatments is not a realistic daily activity. iL Progetto LLC designs whole-home motorized shading systems that integrate with the Crestron, Control4, and Lutron home automation platforms common in Rancho Santa Fe builds, creating scene-based shading programs that adjust every window in a room or a wing simultaneously at the press of a button or on a scheduled basis. The ARB review implications of motorization are neutral — the motors are entirely interior, and the exterior appearance of the shade is unchanged. For the Rancho Santa Fe homeowner who hosts regularly, a hospitality scene that adjusts all shading for afternoon entertaining is a genuine quality-of-life feature. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:plantation-shutters': `Plantation shutters are consistently specified in Rancho Santa Fe's Spanish Colonial and Mediterranean homes because they read as an architecturally integrated element — not a window accessory, but a part of the building — in a way that other treatments rarely achieve. iL Progetto LLC installs solid-basswood shutters custom-milled to the specific window proportions of each estate, with hidden-rod hardware, custom paint matching to existing millwork, and oversized 4.5-inch louvres appropriate for the large-scale fenestration of The Covenant's historic properties. For the Architectural Review Board submissions required in The Covenant, our shutters present as a neutral, traditional exterior element that aligns with the approved architectural character of the neighborhood. We have extensive experience with ARB documentation in Rancho Santa Fe. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:faux-wood-blinds': `Faux-wood blinds rarely enter the conversation for Rancho Santa Fe's primary living spaces, but they perform a specific and important role in the utility-adjacent areas of large estate properties — pool baths, service corridors, staff quarters, garage-entry mudrooms — where the moisture exposure from pool and landscape activity would damage real wood, and where the clean, consistent appearance of a well-made faux-wood blind is the correct call. iL Progetto LLC supplies faux-wood blinds in widths and drops scaled to estate window dimensions, with custom-width capabilities beyond what off-the-shelf programs accommodate. For investment properties and guest houses on Rancho Santa Fe estates — properties that need to look well-maintained without requiring frequent replacement — our moisture-resistant faux-wood line is the durable, presentable choice. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:aluminum-blinds': `Aluminum blinds in Rancho Santa Fe homes are a specialty product deployed in the right context: the architect-designed home office with a floor-to-ceiling glass wall and a need for precise slat-angle light control, the wine cellar anteroom where exact light management is a cellar-quality consideration, or the media room where reflective slat surfaces help bounce ambient light precisely. iL Progetto LLC supplies micro-slat aluminum blinds in custom widths and drops for the large-format windows common in contemporary Rancho Santa Fe builds in Cielo and newer Fairbanks Ranch parcels. In the powder-coat finishes we carry — warm aluminum, champagne, bronze, and matte black — they function as architectural elements as much as window coverings. Slat widths from half-inch to 1-inch available. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:vertical-blinds': `The great room and primary suite glass walls of Rancho Santa Fe's contemporary estate homes — particularly in Cielo, where modern architecture sits alongside more traditional Spanish Colonial builds — often span ten feet or more of floor-to-ceiling glass. iL Progetto LLC installs fabric-vane vertical systems on these large openings in solar-rated sheer and light-filtering constructions, providing the view-preserving glare management that luxury clients expect without the institutional appearance that poorly specified verticals carry. Our headrail hardware is selected for smooth, quiet operation and salt-air resistance at the quality level that Rancho Santa Fe interiors demand. For the contemporary Rancho Santa Fe home where a roller shade would feel too hard-edged, a sheer fabric vertical brings softness while maintaining the clean sightline management the space requires. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:panel-track-blinds': `Panel-track blind systems in Rancho Santa Fe's contemporary estate builds serve as architectural room-dividers as much as window treatments — the large fabric panels, when properly specified, read as designed elements that contribute to the spatial language of the interior. iL Progetto LLC configures panel-track systems for the wide glass walls of Cielo and Fairbanks Ranch contemporary builds, using precision-machined aluminum tracks that operate silently and maintain exact panel alignment at the large scale. Fabric selections for Rancho Santa Fe's luxury market include hand-woven naturals, imported grasscloths, and high-performance solar constructions that address both the aesthetic and functional requirements of these significant windows. For Architectural Review Board documentation, our panel-track systems present a clean, neutral exterior appearance. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:woven-wood-shades': `Woven-wood shades in Rancho Santa Fe find their strongest argument in the hacienda and Mediterranean Revival properties of The Covenant, where the organic textures of bamboo, seagrass, and rattan weaves amplify the hand-applied plaster, terracotta tile, and wrought-iron details that characterize these architecturally significant interiors. iL Progetto LLC sources woven-wood constructions at a quality tier matched to the luxury standard of these homes — substantial weave densities, precise edge finishing, and custom lining options including privacy and blackout liners appropriate for bedroom and media applications. The natural material story also aligns with the landscape character of The Covenant's oak woodland and native garden settings. For the Rancho Santa Fe homeowner working with a designer who specifies authentic natural materials throughout, woven-wood shades are a coherent continuation of that palette. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:sheer-shades': `The private gardens, horse pastures, and mature oak landscapes that surround Rancho Santa Fe estate homes are the point — they are the reason these properties command their prices, and they deserve to be visible from the interior at every waking hour. Sheer shades from iL Progetto LLC provide the soft, diffused light management that luxury interiors require without interrupting the visual connection to those landscapes. The floating vane system allows precise control over glare without requiring the shade to be lowered in a way that blocks the view, making them ideal for the large picture windows and wide glass doors common throughout The Covenant, Cielo, and Del Rayo Estates. We carry this product in a range of warm tones appropriate for Spanish Colonial and contemporary Rancho Santa Fe interiors. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:blackout-curtains': `Blackout curtains in the primary suites of Rancho Santa Fe's estate homes are a sleep-quality investment that the luxury market takes seriously — and the scale of these rooms demands a fabrication approach equal to the interior. iL Progetto LLC custom-fabricates blackout panels with triple-pass blackout interlining, motorized track systems, and face fabrics sourced from our trade-exclusive program in the heavyweight linens, velvets, and performance weaves that luxury bedrooms require. For the properties in The Covenant where the primary suite may have four or five windows with specific proportions dictated by the original architect, we custom-cut every panel to dimension with pattern-matched face fabrics and precisely weighted hems. The exterior appearance of the drapery is planned from the outset to satisfy The Covenant's ARB visual standards. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:sheer-drapes': `Sheer drapery at the estate scale in Rancho Santa Fe is a tailored art form — the wrong weight of fabric on a 14-foot ceiling drapes poorly, the wrong heading on a formal living room looks domestic rather than architectural, and the wrong light transmission turns a carefully designed room flat. iL Progetto LLC fabricates sheer drapery for Rancho Santa Fe's estate homes using heavyweight performance sheers with the body and translucency needed for large-scale formal applications. For the Mediterranean Revival properties in Del Rayo Estates, where windows are frequently arched and deeply recessed, we engineer custom panel shapes and heading solutions that address the geometry without compromising the architectural character. Motorized track options allow sheer and blackout layers to operate independently. Call (858) 338-1678 for an estate consultation.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:motorized-exterior': `Exterior motorized shading on Rancho Santa Fe estate homes presents a specific design challenge: the product must meet The Covenant's Architectural Review Board standards for exterior appearance while delivering the substantial solar heat rejection that the inland San Diego climate demands. iL Progetto LLC navigates ARB submissions for exterior motorized shading routinely, specifying cassette housings in custom-matched powder-coat finishes and screen fabrics in neutral, architecturally appropriate tones that satisfy the review committee. The thermal benefit is significant — exterior roller screens on south and west elevations reduce solar heat gain by up to 80%, meaningfully reducing cooling loads on the large, heavily glazed estate homes in The Covenant and Cielo. Wind sensors and smart-home integration are standard. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:sun-screens': `Exterior solar screens on Rancho Santa Fe estate windows require the same quality of materials and finishing attention that the property's interior receives — these are not utility products bolted onto a window frame, they are architecturally integrated sun-management elements that must hold their appearance through years of the inland San Diego climate. iL Progetto LLC custom-fabricates exterior solar screen frames in powder-coated aluminum precisely sized and finished to match the window and trim details of each estate. In The Covenant, where the ARB reviews any exterior modification, we prepare full submittal documentation and specify only screen fabrics and frame finishes that meet the architectural character of the neighborhood. For the grand south-facing loggia windows of Spanish Colonial Rancho Santa Fe homes, exterior solar screens allow windows to remain open while blocking the solar load that makes those rooms unusable in the afternoon. Call (858) 338-1678.`,

  'rancho-santa-fe:awnings': `A motorized retractable awning over the terrace of a Rancho Santa Fe estate is as much a functional infrastructure element as an architectural accessory — it extends the seasonal usability of outdoor dining and entertaining spaces that may represent a hundred thousand dollars of hardscape and landscaping investment. iL Progetto LLC installs motorized retractable awnings with cassette housings in aluminum finishes custom-matched to the estate's exterior palette. For the Spanish Colonial and Mediterranean properties of The Covenant, we work within ARB submission requirements to specify awning profiles and fabric patterns appropriate to the architectural character of the neighborhood. Our awning fabrics are solution-dyed acrylic rated for UV stability and salt-air resistance over ten-plus-year service lives. Wind sensors, LED lighting integration, and full smart-home compatibility are standard at this level. Call (858) 338-1678.`,
}
